Polish Zloty Advances, Rebounds From Worst Decline in 16 Months

-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 
2011-09-20T07:02:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/polish-zloty-advances-rebounds-from-worst-decline-in-16-months.html
The Polish zloty advances,
rebounding against the euro following its steepest depreciation
in 16 months.  The zloty gained 0.1 percent to 4.3662 against the euro as
of 8:54 a.m. in Warsaw. The currency lost 2.2 percent yesterday,
the most since May 2010, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  